.TH zephyr1 1 "@PROJECT_YEAR@" "@PROJECT_VERSION@" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
zephyr1 \- concatenate files to standard output
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B zephyr1
.RI [ OPTION ]...
.RI [ FILE ]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
Copy each
.I FILE
to standard output in order. If
.I FILE
is a single dash
.RB ( \- ),
read standard input at that position. If no
.I FILE
is given, read standard input once.
.PP
.B zephyr1
is similar in spirit to
.BR cat (1):
it writes the concatenation of inputs to standard output.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Print each file name (or
.RB \(lq standard\ input \(rq
for
.RB \(lq \- \(rq)
to standard error before copying that input.
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Suppress messages that would be printed by
.BR \-\-verbose .
If both
.B \-\-verbose
and
.B \-\-quiet
are given,
.B \-\-quiet
wins.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print a usage summary and exit successfully.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print version and license information and exit successfully.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
An error occurred (invalid options, unreadable file, or I/O error).
.SH AUTHOR
Written by @PROJECT_AUTHOR@ <@PROJECT_EMAIL@>.
